{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":1},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrating from Basic OpMode"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transitioning from basic OpMode development to ARESLib's command-based architecture might seem intimidating, but the benefits in code organization, reusability, and maintainability are enormous. This guide helps you make the leap."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Command-Based Programming?"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Basic OpMode Challenges"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"@TeleOp
public class BasicRobot extends LinearOpMode {
    private DcMotor leftMotor, rightMotor;
    private Servo armServo;

    @Override
    public void runOpMode() {
        // Everything in one place
        leftMotor = hardwareMap.get(DcMotor.class, "left");
        rightMotor = hardwareMap.get(DcMotor.class, "right");
        armServo = hardwareMap.get(Servo.class, "arm");

        waitForStart();

        // Hard to maintain
        while (opModeIsActive()) {
            double drive = gamepad1.left_stick_y;
            double turn = gamepad1.right_stick_x;
            leftMotor.setPower(drive + turn);
            rightMotor.setPower(drive - turn);

            if (gamepad1.a) {
                armServo.setPosition(1.0);
            } else if (gamepad1.b) {
                armServo.setPosition(0.0);
            }
        }
    }
}
"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Problems:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hard to reuse code"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Difficult to test"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No autonomous reuse"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mixed concerns (hardware + logic + controls)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hard to maintain complexity"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command-Based Solutions"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// Separate concerns into clean, reusable components
