"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"02 Dynamic Pathfinding (AD*)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ARESLib includes a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local AD"},{"type":"text","text":"* implementation. If a robot is driving a pre-planned path and encounters an unexpected obstacle (detected via ToF Laser Sensors), it will dynamically route "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"around"},{"type":"text","text":" the obstacle without stopping, then merge back onto the original trajectory."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" Unlike standard A*, AD* is an anytime algorithm. It provides an "optimal enough" path instantly and continues to refine it while the robot is already moving. This allows for collision avoidance at 4+ m/s."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"03 Event Markers (Micro-SOTM)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can trigger logic based on the robot's progress along a path. Common uses in ARESLib:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Spinning up the flywheel"},{"type":"text","text":" 1000ms before reaching the shot location."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deploying the intake"},{"type":"text","text":" while rounding a corner to minimize cycle time."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Seeding the IMU"},{"type":"text","text":" when passing a known landmark or AprilTag."}]}]}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// Retrieving a path from memory
