{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait times for robot charging and Field Management Systems are the enemies of progress. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Championship-grade teams"},{"type":"text","text":" don't wait for hardware to verify their code. They use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Headless JUnit 5"},{"type":"text","text":" tests to validate math, state machines, and physics models in milliseconds."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"01 Why Headless Testing?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Traditional "OpMode testing" requires a physical Control Hub, a charged battery, and minutes of deployment time. Headless testing runs directly on your development machine's CPU."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Speed"},{"type":"text","text":": Run 500+ tests in under 2 seconds."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reliability"},{"type":"text","text":": Tests are deterministic. No mechanical failures or battery drops."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Safe to Fail"},{"type":"text","text":": Test edge cases (like motor stalls or sensor disconnects) that would break a real robot."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"02 The IO Mocking Pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ARESLib enforces a strict "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"IO Abstraction"},{"type":"text","text":". Your subsystem doesn't talk to a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"DcMotor"},{"type":"text","text":"; it talks to an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AresMotorIO"},{"type":"text","text":" interface. This allows us to "swap" the motor for a simulator during testing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" During a match, we inject `DriveIOReal`. During a test, we inject `DriveIOSim`. The subsystem logic never knows the difference, allowing us to verify its behavior with bit-level precision."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// Example: Testing a Swerve Module
@Test
void testModuleAngleTarget() {
    // 1. Setup Mock IO
    var io = new SwerveModuleIOSim();
    var module = new SwerveModule(io);

    // 2. Execute Logic
    module.setTargetState(new SwerveModuleState(1.0, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(90)));
    module.periodic();

    // 3. Verify Result
    // The PID controller should have commanded a voltage
    assertTrue(io.lastVoltage > 0);
}
