"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"04 Pre-Match Diagnostics"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ARESLib includes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AresDiagnostics"},{"type":"text","text":", which runs a "sweep" of all registered mechanisms in the pits. It stresses the arm, drives the chassis 10cm, and spins the intake at 10% power to verify that no cables were loosened during transport."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" If a critical error is detected (like an over-current spike), ARESLib's high-level controllers will automatically scale back voltage commands to prevent permanent motor burnout."}]}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import CodePlayground from '../../components/CodePlayground';"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One of the core tenets of ARESLib is that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Robot Logic should never know what motor it's talking to"},{"type":"text","text":". By using the Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL) and the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"IO"},{"type":"text","text":" pattern, we can run the exact same subsystem code on a real Control Hub, a desktop simulator, or a unit test."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"01 The Blueprint: Logic -> Interface -> Impl"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every subsystem in ARESLib is built using three distinct layers:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" Contains the "Brain." Calculates PID, State Machines, and Kinematics. The "Contract." Defines what data goes in (volts) and what comes out (position). The "Muscle." Either `IOReal` (REV/CANCoder) or `IOSim` (Physics)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"02 Why No "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"DcMotor"},{"type":"text","text":"?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Directly using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"DcMotor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Servo"},{"type":"text","text":" classes in your subsystem makes it impossible to unit test. In ARESLib, we use standardized wrappers:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// The Interface (IO Contract)
public interface DriveIO {
    @AutoLog // Automatically generates Telemetry/Replay fields
    public static class DriveIOInputs {
        public double leftPositionMeters = 0.0;
        public double leftVelocityMetersPerSec = 0.0;
        public double appliedVolts = 0.0;
    }

    public default void updateInputs(DriveIOInputs inputs) {}
    public default void setVoltage(double volts) {}
}
"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"03 Implementing IOReal"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For actual competition, we implement the contract by wrapping the FTC SDK classes. This is the only place in the entire framework where "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"hardwareMap"},{"type":"text","text":" should be touched."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"public class DriveIOReal implements DriveIO {
    private final DcMotorEx leftMotor;

    public DriveIOReal(HardwareMap hwMap) {
        leftMotor = hwMap.get(DcMotorEx.class, "left_drive");
    }

    @Override
    public void updateInputs(DriveIOInputs inputs) {
        inputs.leftPositionMeters = leftMotor.getCurrentPosition() * GEAR_RATIO;
        inputs.leftVelocityMetersPerSec = leftMotor.getVelocity() * GEAR_RATIO;
    }
}
"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"04 Implementing IOSim"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For simulation, we implement the same contract but use a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Physics Model"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of a physical motor. This allows us to practice driving and test autonomous paths without a robot."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" Because the Subsystem only sees the `DriveIO` interface, it behaves identically whether it's getting data from a real encoder or a mathematical model. This is the key to **"Code in Sim, Save at Comp."**"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"05 Interactive Comparison"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"See the difference between traditional and IO pattern approaches yourself:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<CodePlayground title="Traditional vs IO Pattern" initialCode={`// TRADITIONAL APPROACH (Bad) public class BadIntakeSubsystem { private DcMotor motor; // Hard to test!"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":null},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"public BadIntakeSubsystem(HardwareMap hwMap) {
    motor = hwMap.get(DcMotor.class, "intake");
    // No simulation possible
}

public void setPower(double power) {
    motor.setPower(power); // Direct hardware access
}
"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// IO PATTERN APPROACH (Good) public interface IntakeIO { void setVoltage(double volts); void updateInputs(IntakeIOInputs inputs); }"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"public class GoodIntakeSubsystem { private final IntakeIO io; // Hardware-agnostic!"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":null},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"public GoodIntakeSubsystem(IntakeIO io) {
    this.io = io; // Works with real OR sim
}

public void setPower(double power) {
    io.setVoltage(power * 12.0); // Clean abstraction
}
"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"}`} output="╬ô┬ú├┤ Traditional: Locked to hardware ╬ô┬ú├╣ IO Pattern: Testable, Sim-ready, Flexible"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Benefits: ╬ô├ç├│ Unit tests without hardware ╬ô├ç├│ Simulation for autonomous practice ╬ô├ç├│ Easy hardware swapping ╬ô├ç├│ Better code organization" />"}]}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"SystemCheckCommand"},{"type":"text","text":" automates hardware validation before matches, catching issues like disconnected motors, faulty encoders, and battery problems while you still have time to fix them!"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"01 What Are Health Checks?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pre-match health checks automatically verify every subsystem is functioning correctly by:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Battery Voltage Gate"},{"type":"text","text":": Ensures sufficient power for testing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequential Testing"},{"type":"text","text":": Tests each mechanism in isolation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Physical Validation"},{"type":"text","text":": Commands movement and verifies actual response"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Alert System"},{"type":"text","text":": Reports failures immediately"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"02 Quick Start"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2.1 Implement the Interface"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"public class ElevatorSubsystem extends SubsystemBase implements SystemTestable {
    private final ElevatorIO io;

    @Override
    public Command getSystemCheckCommand() {
        return Commands.sequence(
            // Move to known position
            Commands.runOnce(() -> io.setVoltage(6.0)),  // Low voltage for safety
            Commands.waitSeconds(1.0),
            // Verify we moved
            Commands.runOnce(() -> {
                ElevatorIO.ElevatorInputs inputs = new ElevatorIO.ElevatorInputs();
                io.updateInputs(inputs);

                // Check position changed
                assertTrue(inputs.positionMeters > 0.05, 
                          "Elevator not moving - motor or encoder failure!");
            })
        );
    }
}
"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2.2 Create the System Check"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"java"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"// In your OpMode or RobotContainer
